  "rollout_plan_displayname": "Will ship enabled for all users",
  "motivation": "The web, along with computing, is going through one of the biggest foundational changes with the advent of machine learning and large language models.\n\nWhile there is still much to be seen, the trend in agentic browser experimentation points to more and more user journeys depending on the user being logged in to websites.\n\nFederation, one of the most common ways users log in to websites, is largely implemented on top of the browser using low level primitives, so it requires the agentic browser to use what is called “actuation”: computer vision over the DOM to understand what’s going on.\n\nThe problem with “actuation” is that it is an unstructured tool that is by definition statistical, so works within a range of precision and recall.\n\nFor federated login, specifically, we struggled to tolerate that range because it would lead to a known percentage of accidental security incidents.\n\nHow can we give agentic browsers a structured tool to login to websites safely with the user’s federated accounts?",
  "devtrial_instructions": null,
  "activation_risks": "We managed to find a way to pull all of the responsibility to the Identity Provider rather than to the websites, so we expect we'll be able to activate a large part of the web without having to redeploy it.\n\nIt remains to be seen if/how websites are going to perceive agentic browsers logging users in.\n\nIt remains to be seen if/how IdPs are going to proactively support logging in with agentic browsers.",
  "measurement": null,
  "availability_expectation": null,
  "adoption_expectation": null,
  "adoption_plan": null,
  "initial_public_proposal_url": "https://github.com/fedidcg/idp-initiated",
  "explainer_links": [
    "https://github.com/fedidcg/idp-initiated",
    "https://github.com/samuelgoto/proposal-potentially-approved-sites",
    "https://github.com/fedidcg/login-element"
  ],
  "requires_embedder_support": false,
  "spec_link": null,
  "api_spec": false,
  "automation_spec": false,
  "interop_compat_risks": null,
  "all_platforms": null,
  "all_platforms_descr": null,
  "non_oss_deps": null,
  "anticipated_spec_changes": null,
  "security_risks": "We are aware of a false positive and false negative aspect of one of the proposals we have, but we think we have a mechanism that degrades gracefully when we detect these.\n\nWe are going to be monitoring the experiment to understand the extent that these are happening and if users can go through the fallback.",
  "ergonomics_risks": "The proposals being evaluated move all of the required changes to the identity provider and out of websites, since there are many orders of magnitude more of the latter compared to the former.\n\nFor consumers, identity providers are typically well funded and sophisticated web developers, so there isn't any ergonomic risk that we have identified.",
